.DT
teach
Discworld player help
teach

Name
.SI 5
teach - Teach things to other players.
.Ei

Syntax
.SI 5
teach <skill|spell|n levels of skill> to <person(s)>
.EI

Description
.SP 5 5
This command allows you to teach a command, spell or skill to another
player.  In the case of commands and spells the person doing the
teaching needs to be experienced enough in the skill and the person
being taught also needs to be experienced enough to learn and teach
the skill respectively.

In the case of skills the person doing the teaching needs to be a of
a higher level than the person being taught.  The cost in
experience to the teachee is based on the relative levels of the
person teaching and the person being taught.
.EP

Example
.SI 5
> teach judge to khaos
You teach judge to Khaos.
> teach fix to bil
Bil is not high enough level to learn fix.
> teach 1 level of fighting to bil
[Random piece of stuff not included because I cannot remember it]
.EI

See also
.SI 5
commands, spells, learn.
.EI
